		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.00]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Chimi&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>340 is a great haul for one nights work, hell thats a great 2 weeks at level 13ish! You can go 3 routes here:<br><br>1- Armor, When you say you're decked out I asssume you mean in full curscale or similair with perhaps a couple of stat raising items to boot. If you haven't aquired one yet ( and if your scaley/slimey body permits ) get a Foremans Tunic, selling at around 200p. Good AC (12 I think), some decent stat bonuses ( +3 moxie, +3 chutzpah, can't remember exactly), and the best thing of all 0.0 wieght. You gotta love wieghtless armor.<br><br>2- Speaking of wieght, you can take the path or reducing it. If you can save around another 60p you could aquire yourself an evil eye bag which reduces whatever you stick in there by 75%. You'll need to get weight reduction eventually and this is a good first step.<br><br>3-Chopsticks. My first chopstick was a sap of peity I bought for 400p. Slow but damaging. Good off- hand weapon. If you're a well disiplined lizard, you can keep saving whilst you level, until you have enough to purchase a fighting baton, prob for a smooth 800p. This chopstick is kinda overpriced, but with the "monk craze" going on, they are still highly in demand. You also can't neglect the 2H blunts. A bamboo bo stick should run you around 150 give or take. Bought mine for 75p, I think my karma was just good that night though.<br><br>-Chimi, who finds it helpful, from time to time, to throw the pet lizards a bone.</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=rig