		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <span id=>Anonymous</span></a><b><span id=></span></b>
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Anonymous&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>First of all, I was the infamous Iksar MONKey which started this series of replies, but now after some progress, I wanted to check back with a reply to report on my progress.&nbsp;&nbsp;When I wrote the post, I had barely hit 13, and now I'm level 15.  One of my questions was about what I should do with the 340 platium that I picked up, and just the other day, I managed to catch a bargain in purchasing an Essence of Dol (secondary hand - 10 damage, 28 delay) for a mere 150 platium.  On some of the other servers, I've witnessed them being sold at a minimum of 500 platium!  My armor situation is not a problem.  Currently, I have a Lockjaw Tunic and an assembly of Mesh, along with a few other items which sets my stats at: 105 Strength, 80 Stamina, 100 Agility, and 100 Dexterity.  I'd like to think I'm on a good pace here, but with my progress, a few questions have arised.  Now that I have reached level 15, I have Double Attack, and so I put a single point into it to get it started.  That leaves me with nine skill points (five which were from leveling to 14)I don't know what to do with.  I was told my many to stop putting points into Mend once it got very reliable (up to 75 now)and that it would raise it's skill up evenly on it's own.  As for what to do about the left over skill points, I've heard about people saving them until Flying Kick or Instill Doubt, seeing how Flying Kick is your strongest attack and you want it really strong as fast as possible, and Instill Doubt is a difficult skill to raise.  However, the most sound tactic I've heard so far is placing the extra skill points into Feign Death.  Seeing how this is also a difficult skill to raise, it's probably one of the most useful, despite being on a PVP server.  I'm currently in a guild that exists mainly on the mainland, and it's important that I eventually settle down in the Neriak region.  Obviously, I'm going to hafta get good faction, but Feign Death would come in handy quite often in this situation in moving between Cabilis and Neriak.  Of course, I wish for replies, and feel free to add anything else which might be helpful to a level 15 Monk...  Thanks!</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td class=mhback align=right><span class=mh id=fs8><a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=3><img src=/shared/root_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Up" width=17 height=11> Thread Index</a> |  <a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=3&post=1><img src=/shared/new_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="New" width=17 height=11> New Subject</a> | <a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=3&mid=98099514323908&num=4&post=1&mid=98099514323908><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply" width=17 height=11> Reply to Thread</a></span></td></tr><tr><td><table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" class="mform"><tr><td id="fs8">4 Posts [ <a href="/fsearch.html?base=class3">Search Forums</a> ]</nobr></td></tr></table>&nbsp;</td></tr>
